Added because it does not reference a certain ontology, but seems to be a placeholder which points to a list of ontologies (https://obofoundry.org/).In RDF data you might see entries like obo:RO_0001900 which point to an entry in  https://obofoundry.org/ontology/ro.html, which has http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ro.owl# as ontology IRI.
just a redirect to https://www.dublincore.org/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/

all Dublin Core IRIs (e.g. http://purl.org/dc/terms/, http://purl.org/dc/dcam/) point/redirect to https://www.dublincore.org/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/ both DCTerms and DCElements also reference the same terms/elements
